Fedora provides "Vanilla" GNOME & Latest technologies straight
out of the box – just install or try it live. Fedora 36 is now available
and ships GNOME 42, Anaconda Installer provides simple Install
Process, After install, You will guided how to basicly use GNOME,
Good Choise for Modern computers & Beginners.
GNOME can be selected when installing the latest version of
openSUSE. The rolling release of openSUSE Tumbleweed includes
GNOME 42, openSUSE provides "Vanilla" GNOME experience for
more Advanced Users, With YaST, You can configure your system
As you want, Good Choise for Advanced Users.
